annotation.TEXT: Now, this is just a demo, which supposedly contains two worlds, so this shouldn't take terribly long to get through.

Yep! Now, I'm ready to head to the next level, but player 2's been playing long enough for now, so I'm going to reenter the Village and Start+Select out (which I can do since I already "cleared" it by hitting the yellow switch). This will cause the turn to switch.
DOUBLE KILL!
Nuts, I kinda want another fire flower.
One other thing I'm wondering is if the title demo level was changed after recording these inputs, which could've been more fitting in a previous version of the title demo level...
So, let's just let this title demo play out here. Hmm... It's definitely not the original SMW demo's inputs, but Bowser Jr. here doesn't seem to be too enthusiastic about moving forward...
Well, I'm hitting my head on something up there. Wait, let me do a sprinting jump to scroll the screen up...
I wonder if there'll be enough fence koopas for me to get a 1-up combo...
Well, actually, Laharl only slept for 2 years, so Bowser Jr. is a way bigger sleeper!
Nah. I would've been surprised if I actually did find anything there.

Ooh, I block cloned there totally by accident... Nah, that was totally intentional. Alright, let's wait for the Goomba to wake up and then carefully try to block clone the other way to make it symmetrical!
Oh, what? Aw, nuts. I've encountered an invisible wall, so I can go no further. Oh, well.
Huh, is it just me, or did Bowser Jr.'s sprite not change at all after grabbing the mushroom?

...Aw, nuts! Oh, well. I guess that kind of makes sense, so that there's a way out if you already hit the yellow switch (although Start+Select would certainly work in such a case too). Well, let's see what else is around The Village...
BGM: Banjo-Tooie - Hailfire Peaks (Icy Side)
Alright, player 2's turn. Now, player 1 was called "B.JR.", so what'll P2's name be?
Oh, I do believe these Pokeys can be made to perfectly overlap if I wait long enough...
Hmm... A dead end, perhaps? Is the title demo done now?
"U. C."... I believe that means "Under construction".
Hmm... BJ's kind of in the way, but I'm pretty sure that says, "The power of the switch you have pushed will turn into solid blocks."
Blue Yoshi 815 asked me to try out this hack not too long ago, and I've decided to start it now.
I wonder why there are no enemies...
Alright, got all of the ! coins.
So, I guess I get to slide-kill some stuff to begin with here.
If I lure that Pokey over here, I can slide-kill it.
Aw, what's with the unhappy wall triangle?
Nuts. Oh, but I can just jump back up and try again. I'll try getting max running speed for my next attempt.
Yeah, that "shortcut" was pointless. It might be slightly useful for speedrunning, but I'm not speedrunning here.
That was nice, but now I'm getting low on time...
Move faster, Pokey! I want to slide-kill you here!
Yo, dude. You missed a couple of ? blocks back there...
That's weird. Why are the "DE" letters in "DEMO" going behind layer 1 objects?
DOUBLE KILL!
Goal tape average so far: 40 / 1 = 40 stars each.
...Nah, not really. It's just a hack made by someone named BBKaizo. So, welcome to Bowser Jr.'s Adventure!
LOL at the text in the ground there!
Nuts, can't place any calls at the phone booth there. Oh, another door.
And then after this, I'll probably start playing that new version of Super Tweak World that waffledoctor87 sent me.
Nice x2.
Yes, finally. Alright, let's get this game started now.
Well, there's a mushroom.

Huh, "Double Player", eh? So, that's what the 2-player mode is called in this hack, I guess. And, actually, I am curious what player 2's version of Bowser Jr. is called and what he looks like, so I'll choose "Double Player" here!
...It's "B.JR." as well. Alright, let's ludicrously speed through that "Desert Ruins" area again. (That's what the .txt file with all the song names calls this area.)
Hello, this is SomeGuy712x, and welcome to a Kaizo hack!
So, yeah. I ended up here again. Well, let's exit via the pipe on the right again, and see if there's anything else in The Village.
Uh, oh. A Lava Lotus. Those are slide-killable, but only if they're close enough to slopes (or if I have a cape, but that seems unlikely in this hack).
Well, I wasn't expecting this to be what the inside of that house looked like!
Nuts. I kind of want that mushroom, so I'm not getting very many coins from that multi-coin block.
Heh. That Lava Lotus is on a slope. Be careful, though. Sliding doesn't work on their fireballs.
Aw, what's with the unhappy cloud? Also, is this the end of the line or something?
Of course, the yellow switch is gone now, since it's already been activated. Now, let's see what's through the pipe to the right...
So, I guess we'll look at The Village first.
I wonder if there's anything good in that turn block square...
I'm still bothered by the fact that Bowser Jr.'s sprite still looks the same whether you're small or super.
Huh? So, he took a 5-year nap or something? What is this, Disgaea?
...Except for this yellow one at the top. Huh. I could also go through the pipe on the right instead...
Does this level have side exits enabled?
BGM: Cave Story - On To Grasstown
Not hitting that turn block? Okay, whatever. So, it's been about 1½ minutes so far...
What, a vine? Oh, then that must mean...
Okay, I'm going to activate the switch now, and then have player 2 run through here again to see what's in the pipe on the right.
BGM: Bahamut Lagoon - Desert Daphira
Whoa, a fire flower! So there are non-mushroom power ups in this hack! (So, maybe there's a possibility of there being capes later on...)
Pfft... I meant to bounce high off of that mole to get up there.

Oh, a pipe! It would've been better if that pipe extended low enough so that it would be visible without scrolling the screen up. Either that or set the level to "Vertical scroll at will", though that might've made the "HI" and "LOL" in the ground earlier harder to see.
To be continued... Yo!
I guess this level's main theme is slide-killing things!
Aw, I was hoping that that was a multi-coin block.
Well, who knows, because the demo only hit 3 of the 16 blocks there...
Well, at least I was able to slide-jump up here. Too bad I can't slide-kill that Sumo Brother, since there are no slopes nearby. (Actually, I don't think Sumo Brothers are slide-killable anyway.)
Alright, BJ1's turn. Let's check out Sky Mountain.
Yeah, it's looking like the only power ups in this hack are mushrooms.
And here's the overworld. Now, this hack comes with a .txt file that lists the music used in the hack, so that's pretty nice.

How long is this title demo anyway? It's been going on for about a minute now, but hasn't been terribly interesting, and BJ's making some moves that are making me wonder if the demo recording desynched or something...
Ow, the extreme corner of my hitbox! I probably would've avoided that if BJ got visibly taller while super...
BGM: Super Mario Sunshine - Bianco Hills
Oh, I think I can totally jump over that wall there!
So, I guess we collect ! coins in this hack instead of Yoshi coins. Also, I wonder if this is one of those hacks where mushrooms are the only power ups...
Go, my yellow ! blocks, and fill the world with your yellowness!
That unlocked Chuck's Cave, which I'll be playing next time, using BJ2! (But, if something unfortunate should happen to BJ2, then BJ1 will be ready to take over!)

Ow... It's like he didn't even try to jump over those munchers. I wonder if the title demo will end up dying? That would be silly, and it's also a big no-no in a hack, because then the player would become stuck in the title demo level.
Looks like "MH", and that's it. Any idea what "MH" stands for?
Well, that's probably gonna be annoying if I can't tell whether BJ's super or not just by looking at his sprite...
Fortunately, the goal's right there. However, I think the mole holes are spelling something beneath the goal... "MU"...?
Ow, my jaws of life!
Ooh, looks like a beach. (The song name .txt file calls this area "The Beach", so there you go.)
...Yep, the block has a 1-up.
So much slide-killing!
Hmm... I'm guessing fire flowers are rare, since most power up blocks have given me only mushrooms.
Nice.
That was close. If that Lava Lotus fired just as I slid into it, I'm sure I would've been hit.
I wonder if this vine leads to anything interesting...
Ah, a door.
BGM: MegaMari - Cirno's Stage
Hey there, text in the ground! How's it going?
Um, what? Well, suddenly, there are switch palace switches, but they're all unreachable...
I wonder if maybe this level was placed here just as an optional "bonus" thing since this is a demo, and maybe in the full version, this will be a proper castle level or something later on...
I wonder if anyone's home, or if I can even enter that door...
This looks like it should maybe be a whole separate level.
Aha, I had a sneaking suspicion that there was stuff up here.
Hahah, made it! Level... not so broken!
Ow, my prime ribs!
Nuts. There were only seven fence koopas, and this last red one isn't even stompable, so I could only get up to "4000" in the combo.
BARF! I pressed my luck too much with those close calls and finally hit a whammy there...
BTW, "Bianco" in "Bianco Hills" is misspelled as "Bianico" in the song name .txt file.
I thought I was gonna miss the goal tape there, but I guess the extreme corner of my hitbox managed to just barely clip it.
I'm just looking at the color differences between the two players here. (Yes, it says "Mario" and "Luigi" there. I guess BBKaizo didn't think to change that text.)
Maybe I can get the camera position down a little bit so I can see the letters better...
